HEADWORD: Memento mori
<hw>Me*men"to mo"ri</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>Lit.,
remember to die, i.e., that you must die; a warning to be prepared for
death; an object, as a death's-head or a personal ornament, usually
emblematic, used as a reminder of death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meminna</ent>⟦br⟧
